```

## Why This Was Failing

**Before (WRONG):**
- User visits `readyio.com`
- Config says: `API_BASE_URL = https://readyio.com/api`
- Frontend tries to call: `https://readyio.com/api/site/by-domain`
- **But your backend is NOT at `readyio.com`!** ❌

**After (CORRECT):**
- User visits `readyio.com`
- Config says: `API_BASE_URL = https://igrowbig.com/api`
- Frontend tries to call: `https://igrowbig.com/api/site/by-domain`
- Backend receives request with header: `X-Tenant-Domain: readyio.com`
- Backend looks up `readyio.com` in database and returns tenant data ✅

## Architecture Explanation
```
┌─────────────────────┐
│  readyio.com        │ ← Custom Domain (Frontend only)
│  (User visits here) │
└──────────┬──────────┘
           │
           │ Makes API call to:
           │ https://igrowbig.com/api/site/by-domain
           │ Header: X-Tenant-Domain: readyio.com
           ▼
┌─────────────────────┐
│  igrowbig.com/api   │ ← Backend API (Always here)
│  (Node.js server)   │
└──────────┬──────────┘
           │
           │ Queries database for tenant with
           │ custom_domain = 'readyio.com'
           ▼
┌─────────────────────┐
│  MySQL Database     │
│  (tbl_tenants)      │
└─────────────────────┘